Apranga, Baltic Clothing Retailer, Sees 2011 Sales Rising 11%

-- B y   M i l d a   S e p u t y t e
-- 
2011-02-23T12:24:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/apranga-baltic-clothing-retailer-sees-2011-sales-rising-11-.html
Apranga AB, the biggest Baltic
clothing retailer, estimated sales may rise an annual 11 percent
this year on recovering demand in the region.  Revenue may rise to 420 million litai ($167 million), the
Vilnius-based company said in a statement to the stock exchange
today. The clothing chain, which operates 115 stores in Estonia,
Latvia and  Lithuania , plans to add from 5 to 8 new shops this
year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Milda Seputyte in Vilnius at 
 mseputyte@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net  